10/04/2011
ANKARA, Turkey -- A gunman shot and killed the head of the Social Security Institution in the southern province of Mugla on Friday (April 8th) during a meeting of regional officials. 
The assailant surrendered to police after briefly taking three hostages, who were released unharmed. 
The victim worked at the local social security institution and reportedly was a colleague of the gunman. 
(Anadolu news agency, CNN Turk, Hurriyet - 08/04/11)
